@MassiveStarGuy Would your C code evaluate the whole thing?

if a is None then dataframe.iloc[a] WILL FAIL and give you a TypeError because indices have to be integers. 

BUT if you check a is None first and the condition fails, the if statement will NOT try to do dataframe.iloc[a] and therefore you won't encounter the error :)

2/2

@python_tip of the day!

Conditions in an if statement will be checked IN ORDER and AS SOON as the condition is not met it will STOP evaluating...

So you can write
if a is not None and dataframe.iloc[a]>0
  
but NOT
if dataframe.iloc[a]>0 and a is not None

Happy mentoring! And if you're an experienced mentor what advice would you give young leaders? 🤔

7/7

Even if the meeting was 5 minutes long and everything is going well, I remind them that if they need me they can email me. It feels repetitive, you might even feel stupid saying it everytime. But one day your student might be in a crisis and not know what to do...

6/

Ask them what they need. Familiarise yourself with the resources available within the uni and sign post them. Be honest. If you know they're shit tell them, and empower them to get the help they deserve.

3️⃣ "You can drop me an email anytime" 

I say this at every meeting. 

5/

And having an ear to listen, or someone to just help you get your thoughts together, is often all you need. But if a student is going through a rougher patch, you're not meant to have all the answers - YOUR ARE NOT TRAINED for this.  So what's YOUR job in that situation?

4/

b) it can tell you a lot about how they see and approach the world - which will help you understand and address their needs.

2️⃣ Listen, but remember you're not their therapist 🙏

If you've built trust with your students they might enjoy and feel comfortable talking to you. 

3/

1️⃣ Your students are ✨people✨

Yes you need to talk about their assignments and see if they're on track and you want to help them academically. But showing an interest in them as people, in what they enjoy and what they don't does two things: 
a) it builds raport and TRUST
